            , <rs id="t18160214-98-viclabel575" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160214-98-victim1046 t18160214-98-viclabel575"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-98-person1047">
                  MARY 
                  ANN NIXON
               <interp inst="t18160214-98-person1047" type="surname" value="ANN NIXON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-98-person1047" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-98-person1047" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lost these things on the 30th of September. I had met the prisoner, and walked with him in the city and <placeName id="t18160214-98-crimeloc576">Islington-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18160214-98-crimeloc576" type="placeName" value="Islington-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18160214-98-crimeloc576" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160214-98-off573 t18160214-98-crimeloc576"></join>, fourteen or fifteen times previous to the 38th of September, when I asked him home, it was about nine o'clock at night, and left him in my room while I went out for some porter. On my return again, I met him coming out, and asked him if he was going to stay, and he said he would return again in a minute. On my going up stairs I missed my property in question from the table drawer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-98-person1048">
